div1.p: Territory of Washington Third Judicial District } ss. No.4704
To the Sheriff of Pierce County, Greeting:

WHEREAS, C.H. Hutchinson recovered judgment against W.H. Harris in the District Court for the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, on the 13th day of November A.D. 1885 for the sum of Dollars, with interest at the rate of until paid, and cost of suit, amounting to Seventeen and 40/100 ($17.40) Dollars. and Increased cost taxed at Jan and 75/100 ($10. 45/100) dollars. THEREFORE, in the name of the United States of America, you are hereby commanded forthwith to levy upon, seize and take into execution, the personal property of the said W.H. Harris in your County, sufficient subject to execution to satisfy said judgment, interest and increased interest, cost and increased cost, and make sale therof according to law; and if sufficient personal property cannot be found, then you are further commanded to make the amount of saif judgment, interest and increased interest, cost and increased cost, out of his real property, not exempt by law, and make retun of this writ within sixty days drom the date hereof.
Herein fail not and have you then and there this writ
WITNESS the Hon. Roger S. Greene, Chief Justice of the Supreme Court, and Judge of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, and the Seal of said Court, this 3rd day of December A.D. 1885
By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
Settled in full Jan, 22nd 1886 Lewis Bryd Sheriff of Pierce Co. W.T.
Re & Dec 4th 1885: Bryd Sheriff Pierce Co. W.T.
IN THE DISTRICT COURT, THIRD JUDICIAL DISTRICT
In Re, the petition of C.W. Hutchinson VS. for Writ of Habeas Corpus
Judgment for $ Interest at per cent, $ Increased Interest, $ Cost, $17.40 Clerk's Incresed Cpst $ 3.40 Sherif's Increased Costs of King County $7.35 Service 1.00 Mileage 10.00 1.00 .30 30.45
Filed 188 JAMES SEAVVEY, Clerk By Deputy
FILED JAN 25 1886 James Seavey Clerk, By James P. Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
